<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="678" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24557H/5–1948: Airgram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Huston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-19">May 19,
                                1948</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <gloss target="#t_A1">A–273</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 115, March 11, 1947. FoMin Lange told Ambassador Bay
                            yesterday, in reply to a question, that there have been no developments
                            whatever in the Spitsbergen question since the despatch of his letter to
                            Molotov last year conveying Norway’s refusal to enter into negotiations
                            looking to the joint defense of the archipelago. Mr. Lange indicated
                            that he considered the subject “dead”, at least for the time being.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>